io USA'' in Japan.</ref>\n<ref name=\"ref2\">Titled as ''Super Mario Bros. 2'' in Japan.</ref>\n<ref name=ref3>A [[Family Computer Disk System]] port of the arcade edition titled ''Vs. Clu Clu Land''.</ref>\n<ref name=snk>Originally exlusive to Western regions, but was eventually released in Japan on February 19, 2020.</ref>\n}}\n\n==== SNES games ====\nAnnounced in a [[Nintendo Direct]] on September 4, 2019, SNES games were added to the service worldwide with 20 titles on September 5, 2019.<ref name=\"snes\"/> They are available in a separate app from NES games. Games available include:\n\n{| class =\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+List of Super NES games on Nintendo Switch Online\n!Release date\n!Game\n!Publisher\n!NA/PAL/KR\n!JP/HK\n|-\n| rowspan=\"21\" |September 5, 2019\n|''[[Brawl Brothers]]''\n|City Connection\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Breath of Fire (video game)|Breath of Fire]]''\n|Capcom\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Demon's Crest]]''\n|Capcom\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[F-Zero (video game)|F-Zero]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Joe & Mac 2: Lost in the Tropics]]''\n|[[G-Mode]]\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Kirby's Dream Course]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Kirby's Dream Land 3]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[The Legend of Zelda: A Link to the Past]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Pilotwings (video game)|Pilotwings]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''Smash Tennis''\n|[[Bandai Namco]]\n|{{ya}} {{r|ref4|group=lower-alpha}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Star Fox (1993 video game)|Star Fox]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Stunt Race FX]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Earth Defense Force (video game)|Super E.D.F. Earth Defense Force]]''\n|City Connection\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Super Ghouls 'n Ghosts]]''\n|Capcom\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Super Mario Kart]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Super Mario World]]''\n|Nintendo\n|{{ya}}\n|{{ya}}\n|-\n|''[[Yoshi's Island|Super Mario World 2: Yoshi's Isla