| date = September 16, 2018 | accessdate =September 16, 2018 | work = [[Destructoid]] }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/nintendo-switch-onlines-first-special-offers-revea/1100-6461782/|title=Nintendo Switch Online's First \"Special Offers\" Revealed|last=Knezevic|first=Kevin|date=September 14, 2018|website=GameSpot|language=en-US|accessdate=February 6, 2019}}</ref> specifically intended for use with the aforementioned NES app.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}} Similarly, a special wireless SNES-based controller designed to work with the Switch was made available to purchase exclusively to Online subscribers shortly after the service added support for SNES titles.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.polygon.com/2019/9/4/20849110/nintendo-switch-snes-wireless-controllers-price-release-date | title = SNES-style wireless controllers confirmed for the Nintendo Switch | first = Charlie | last= Hall | date =September 4, 2019 | accessdate = September 6, 2019 | work = [[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] }}</ref>\n\nCoinciding with the anticipated release of ''[[Super Mario Maker 2]]'', a price-reduction promotion was announced during the game's [[Nintendo Direct]] that was available exclusively to Nintendo Switch Online members. The promotion introduced \"Nintendo Switch Game Vouchers\", which allows purchasers to download two qualifying Nintendo Switch games for a set price of $99.99 MSRP, compared to a $120 sum of buying both games separately.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/deals/2019/5/16/18627669/nintendo-switch-online-game-vouchers-deal|title=Nintendo offers \u2018game vouchers\u2019 to Switch Online members|last=Heller|first=Emily|date=2019-05-16|website=Polygon|access-date=2019-05-23}}</ref>\n\nNintendo has also offered free original games for those with an Online subscription. ''[[Tetris 99]]'' was released as a free to play title for subscribers in February 2019, though has subsequently offered paid downloadable content and retail versions of the game for non-subscribers.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.engadget.com/2019/05/10/nintendo-tetris-99-big-block-dlc-offline/ | title = Nintendo will let you play 'Tetris 99' offline for $10 | first= Steve | last= Dent | date = May 10, 2019 | accessdate = September 6, 2019 | work = [[Engadget]] }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Nintendo Switch}}\n\n[[Category:2018 introductions]]\n[[Category:Nintendo emulators]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Entertainment System]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Entertainment System emulators]]\n[[Category:Nintendo services]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch]]\n[[Category:Online video game services]]\n[[Category:Super Nintendo Entertainment System]]\n[[Category:Super Nintendo Entertainment System emulators]]\n[[Category:Video game platform emulators]]\n\n[[de:Nintendo Switch#Nintendo Switch Online]]\n", "name_user": "2600:8807:9940:e5d9:d557:5939:9c77:190e", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(This page clearly isn't blank. Do you want uncited in an article?)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nintendo_Switch_Online"}
